roughly ten years ago?

04:33.022 --> 04:34.774
-Really?
-[man] I'm just asking.

04:34.857 --> 04:37.193
That's how they're gonna start?
Dad, come on.

04:38.278 --> 04:43.074
It doesn't necessarily mean that
it'll be like that in the trial, Owen,

04:44.117 --> 04:47.578
but, uh, sometimes prosecutors, they...

04:47.662 --> 04:50.373
they try atypical inroads...

04:52.083 --> 04:53.167
to crack you.

04:53.251 --> 04:56.838
That's why we...
we have to prep for the unexpected.

04:58.756 --> 04:59.841
Can you resume, please?

05:00.216 --> 05:03.303
Have you ever been hospitalized
for mental illness?

05:11.936 --> 05:13.563
Yes, ten years ago.

05:13.938 --> 05:15.857
Please explain what happened.

05:16.858 --> 05:18.776
[Owen] I was hospitalized...

05:19.610 --> 05:20.945
and medicated...

05:22.905 --> 05:23.948
and...

05:26.826 --> 05:31.956
that was the last episode I had.

05:32.457 --> 05:34.959
Wasn't the nature
of this psychosis delusional?

05:35.043 --> 05:38.463
That you sometimes thought you saw
your brother when he wasn't there?

05:39.130 --> 05:40.173
[Owen] Not exactly.

05:41.299 --> 05:42.383
Just say no.

05:43.343 --> 05:45.553
Then what was the nature
of this psychosis?

05:58.733 --> 06:02.779
[sighs] Owen, don't you think
that your mental illness

06:02.862 --> 06:06.199
should disqualify you from testifying
as a witness on your brother's behalf?

06:06.282 --> 06:09.118
Look, there's only one question here
that really matters.

06:09.202 --> 06:11.829
Owen, do you know what is real?

06:18.711 --> 06:19.879
One hundred percent.

06:21.923 --> 06:23.508
I'm<i> compos mentis.</i>

06:28.763 --> 06:30.640
[woman] Welcome to New York.

06:30.890 --> 06:35.812
And this is Statue of Extra Liberty. <i>Da.</i>

06:37.772 --> 06:40.108
Statue of Extra Liberty. Okay.

06:40.191 --> 06:42.151
[woman continues speaking in Russian]

06:44.612 --> 06:46.614
[foghorn blares]

06:48.574 --> 06:51.244
[man] How'd the trial prep go
for a naughty brother?

06:52.328 --> 06:53.704
Did you tell them about me?

06:54.622 --> 06:56.332
You're not supposed to be here.

06:56.416 --> 06:59.252
[man] Good.
You're still using the code words,

06:59.335 --> 07:01.295
even though I am technically invisible.

07:02.296 --> 07:05.383
Owen, this week must be
a doozy for you, huh?

07:05.800 --> 07:08.803
You thought you were rid of me,
but I have new information.

07:10.430 --> 07:11.556
This time I know.

07:17.562 --> 07:19.439
You've been chosen to save the world.

07:20.857 --> 07:22.024
You're gonna be a hero.

07:22.108 --> 07:23.401
[foghorn blares]

07:23.484 --> 07:25.236
I don't want this. I don't want it.

07:26.279 --> 07:27.113
I don't want this.

07:27.196 --> 07:30.783
The details of the mission will be
delivered to you by an agent, a woman.

07:30.867 --> 07:32.493
You'll know her
when you see her, trust me.

07:33.035 --> 07:34.412
Just make contact with her.

07:35.163 --> 07:36.539
The pattern is the pattern.

07:38.124 --> 07:40.251
She'll reach you for further instructions!

07:41.043 --> 07:42.420
